rComments: Great facilitator of conversation. Draws insight out of you rather than disseminating information. Reserved...but thoughtful, kind, and an interesting sense of humour once you get to know her

Had tendency to run off topic. Very poor quality lecturer, quite boring actually (many sleepy people by end of class). Assignments vague and repetitive. Very difficult to get a hold of her for help. Grades based on how much she likes you. Don't go to this class without a full cup of strong coffee!
ya, that's a good word for her-- smug.
